1 Section 1. NRS 361A.030 is hereby amended to read as
2 follows:
3 361A.030 1. “Agricultural use” means the current
4 employment of real property as a business venture for profit, which
5 business produced a minimum gross income of $5,000 from
6 agricultural pursuits during the immediately preceding calendar year
7 by:
8 (a) Raising, harvesting and selling crops, fruit, flowers, timber
9 and other products of the soil;
10 (b) Feeding, breeding, management and sale of livestock,
11 poultry, or the produce thereof, if the real property used therefor is
12 owned or leased by the operator and is of sufficient size and
13 capacity to produce more than one-half of the feed required during
14 that year for the agricultural pursuit;
15 (c) Operating a feed lot consisting of at least 50 head of cattle or
16 an equivalent number of animal units of sheep or hogs, for the
17 production of food;
18 (d) Raising furbearing animals or bees;
19 (e) Dairying and the sale of dairy products; or
20 (f) Any other use determined by the Department to constitute
21 agricultural use if such use is verified by the Department.
22  The term includes every process and step necessary and incident
23 to the preparation and storage of the products raised on such
24 property for human or animal consumption or for marketing except
25 actual market locations.
26 2. As used in this section [, “current] :
27 (a) “Agrivoltaic purposes” means a system under which solar
28 energy production and agricultural production, including crop or
29 animal production, occurs in an integrated manner on the same
30 piece of land.
31 (b) “Current employment” of real property in agricultural use
32 includes:
33 [(a)] (1) Land lying fallow for 1 year as a normal and regular
34 requirement of good agricultural husbandry;
35 [(b)] (2) Land planted in orchards or other perennials prior to
36 maturity; [and
37 (c)] (3) Land leased or otherwise made available for use by an
38 agricultural association formed pursuant to chapter 547 of NRS [.] ;
39 and
40 (4) Land used for agrivoltaic purposes.
